  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 857669,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "HackerOne community member rajib_mahmud has reported a missing validation of user input when saving delivery limitations in Revive Adserver 6.0.6 and earlier. A low\u2011privileged user could add an unexpected `component` parameter and inject malicious PHP code into the `compiledlimitations` field, which would then be executed during banner delivery.\n\nInput sanitisation has been improved to ensure that unexpected parameters are filtered out.",
